Each creature a verse in Nature's hymn.

A place of wonder and pure grace.
Nature, you are my solace, my muse,
Your beauty reflected in every one of us.

So here I stand, humbled by your might,
Entranced by the radiant daylight.
For in your arms, I find peace, I find home,
In Nature's hands, solace roams.
